> **Strategic Takeaway:** Total per person: 283 hours a year. For a team of five: 1,415 hours a year. That is 0.68 FTE. More than half a full-time person spent on disconnection. The integration cost was $30,000. The annual value of recovered time was estimated at $90,000. The payback period was under four months. The teams that accept disconnection are the ones paying the quiet cost. The teams that integrate are the ones reclaiming the time. Measure the disconnection time. Integrate the tools. Reclaim the hours.

